The paper deals with secure communication over a wiretap channel with side information, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the concept of secure coding and information-theoretic security, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Gaussian distributions and optimization techniques suggests a connection to machine learning and signal processing (cs.MM). The presence of side information and the use of joint source-channel coding suggest a connection to information theory and communication systems (cs.SI). Finally, the use of digital and analog signals and the analysis of distortion under SNR mismatch suggest a connection to the field of signal processing and machine learning (cs.LG).
